    "power_data_west['month'] = power_data_west['end'].dt.strftime('%b')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from calendar import month_abbr\n",
    "\n",
    "lower_ma = [m.lower() for m in month_abbr]\n",
    "\n",
    "# one-liner with Pandas\n",
    "power_data_west['month_int'] = power_data_west['month'].str.lower().map(lambda m: lower_ma.index(m)).astype('Int8')"
   ]
  },
  {

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pandas.tseries.holiday import USFederalHolidayCalendar as calendar\n",
    "\n",
    "date_range = pd.date_range(start='2019-01-01', end='2022-01-27')\n",
    "\n",
    "cal = calendar()\n",
    "holidays = cal.holidays(start=date_range.min(), end=date_range.max())\n",
    "\n",
    "power_data_west['holiday'] = power_data_west['end'].dt.date.astype('datetime64').isin(holidays)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "for i in range(1, 10):\n",
    "    power_data_west_24[\"demand_lag_{}\".format(i)] = power_data_west_24['demand'].shift(i)\n",
    "    power_data_west_24[\"temp_lag_{}\".format(i)] = power_data_west_24['temp'].shift(i)\n",
    "    power_data_west_24[\"humidity_lag_{}\".format(i)] = power_data_west_24['humidity'].shift(i)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "def timeseries_train_test_split(X, y, test_size):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # get the index after which test set starts\n",
    "    test_index = int(len(X)*(1-test_size))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    X_train = X.iloc[:test_index]\n",
    "    y_train = y.iloc[:test_index]\n",
    "    X_test = X.iloc[test_index:]\n",
    "    y_test = y.iloc[test_index:]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "dataset.kW.plot()"
   ]

    "def plotModelTrainingResults(model, X_train_scaled=X_train_scaled, y_train_scaled=y_train_scaled):\n",
    "  \n",
    "    prediction = model.predict(X_train_scaled)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    prediction = prediction.reshape((758,))\n",
    "    y_train_scaled = y_train_scaled.reshape((758,))\n",

    "    print('shape of y_train', y_train.shape)\n",
    "    print('shape of prediction', prediction.shape)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))\n",
    "    plt.plot(prediction, label=\"prediction\", linewidth=2.0)\n",
    "    plt.plot(y_train_scaled, label=\"actual\", linewidth=2.0, alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "    mape_error_var = mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_train_scaled, prediction)\n",
    "    mae_error_var = mean_absolute_error(y_train_scaled, prediction)\n",
    "    mse_error_var = mean_squared_error(y_train_scaled, prediction, squared=True)\n",
    "    rmse_error_var = mean_squared_error(y_train, prediction, squared=False)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.title(\"Mean absolute percentage error {0:.2f}%\".format(mape_error_var))\n",
    "    plt.legend(loc=\"best\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.grid(True);\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results = pd.DataFrame({'Actual':y_train_scaled, \n",
    "                            'Prediction':prediction  \n",
    "                           })\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results, mape_error_var, mae_error_var, mse_error_var, rmse_error_var\n",
    "    \n",
    "train_results, train_mape_error_var, train_mae_error_var, train_mse_error_var, train_rmse_error_var = plotModelTrainingResults(svr_model)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "def plotModelPredictions(model, X_train=X_train, X_test_scaled=X_test_scaled, y_test_scaled=y_test_scaled):\n",
    "  \n",
    "    prediction = model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    prediction = prediction.reshape((326,))\n",
    "    y_test_scaled = y_test_scaled.reshape((326,))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))\n",
    "    plt.plot(prediction, label=\"prediction\", linewidth=2.0)\n",
    "    plt.plot(y_test_scaled, label=\"actual\", linewidth=2.0, alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "    mape_error_var = mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_test, prediction)\n",
    "    mae_error_var = mean_absolute_error(y_test, prediction)\n",
    "    mse_error_var = mean_squared_error(y_test, prediction, squared=True)\n",
    "    rmse_error_var = mean_squared_error(y_test, prediction, squared=False)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.title(\"Mean absolute percentage error {0:.2f}%\".format(mape_error_var))\n",
    "    plt.legend(loc=\"best\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.grid(True);\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results = pd.DataFrame({'Actual':y_test_scaled, \n",
    "                            'Prediction':prediction  \n",
    "                           })\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results, mape_error_var, mae_error_var, mse_error_var, rmse_error_var\n",
    "    \n",
    "results, mape_error_var, mae_error_var, mse_error_var, rmse_error_var = plotModelPredictions(svr_model)"
   ]
  },
